node.text:
For #WorldRefugeeDay, I got the chance to swap stories of home with an incredible person. @mi.nnie_san lives in Denver, but was born in a refugee camp.⁣
⁣
It was a moving experience for me and a reminder that we all have a part to play making sure @refugees feel welcome.⁣
⁣
#WithRefugees #RefugeeDay

node.text: I love the beaches of California (El Matador is my favorite, visit this summer if you’re in LA!), but I miss my Boston beaches too. I commissioned this painting of Gloucester Beach from the incredibly talented artist @kristentirneyart. It’s the beach at night with a blood moon, and it reminds me of home. Kristen is known for her serene seascapes but I love that this one is a bit dramatic. She captures the movement of the waves at night in such a beautiful way. Check her out!
